fields.description: Codec name used to encode audio for transmission on the network. Possible values are: unknown, invalid, cn, pcma, pcmu, amrWide, g722, g7221, g7221c, g729, multiChannelAudio, muchv2, opus, satin, satinFullband, rtAudio8, rtAudio16, silk, silkNarrow, silkWide, siren, xmsRta, unknownFutureValue.
fields.name: AudioCodec

fields.description: Average jitter for the stream computed as specified in RFC 3550, denoted in ISO 8601 format. For example, 1 second is denoted as 'PT1S', where 'P' is the duration designator, 'T' is the time designator, and 'S' is the second designator.
fields.name: AverageAudioNetworkJitter

fields.description: Average estimated bandwidth available between two endpoints in bits per second.
fields.name: AverageBandwidthEstimate

fields.description: Average duration of the received freezing time in the video stream.
fields.name: AverageFreezeDuration

fields.description: Average jitter for the stream computed as specified in RFC 3550, denoted in ISO 8601 format. For example, 1 second is denoted as 'PT1S', where 'P' is the duration designator, 'T' is the time designator, and 'S' is the second designator.
fields.name: AverageJitter

fields.description: Average network propagation round-trip time computed as specified in RFC 3550, denoted in ISO 8601 format. For example, 1 second is denoted as 'PT1S', where 'P' is the duration designator, 'T' is the time designator, and 'S' is the second designator.
fields.name: AverageRoundTripTime

fields.description: UTC time when the stream ended. The DateTimeOffset type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z. This field is only available for streams that use the SIP protocol.
fields.name: EndDateTime

fields.description: Indicates whether the forward error correction (FEC) was used at some point during the session. The default value is null.
fields.name: IsAudioForwardErrorCorrectionUsed

fields.description: Maximum of audio network jitter computed over each of the 20 second windows during the session, denoted in ISO 8601 format. For example, 1 second is denoted as 'PT1S', where 'P' is the duration designator, 'T' is the time designator, and 'S' is the second designator.
fields.name: MaxAudioNetworkJitter

fields.description: Maximum jitter for the stream computed as specified in RFC 3550, denoted in ISO 8601 format. For example, 1 second is denoted as 'PT1S', where 'P' is the duration designator, 'T' is the time designator, and 'S' is the second designator.
fields.name: MaxJitter

fields.description: Maximum network propagation round-trip time computed as specified in RFC 3550, denoted in ISO 8601 format. For example, 1 second is denoted as 'PT1S', where 'P' is the duration designator, 'T' is the time designator, and 'S' is the second designator.
fields.name: MaxRoundTripTime

fields.description: The OData ID of this entity
fields.name: ODataId

fields.description: The OData Type of this entity
fields.name: ODataType

fields.description: Average duration of the received freezing time in the video stream represented in root mean square.
fields.name: RmsFreezeDuration

fields.description: UTC time when the stream started. The DateTimeOffset type represents date and time information using ISO 8601 format and is always in UTC time. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 is 2014-01-01T00:00:00Z. This field is only available for streams that use the SIP protocol.
fields.name: StartDateTime

fields.description: Codec name used to encode video for transmission on the network. Possible values are: unknown, invalid, av1, h263, h264, h264s, h264uc, h265, rtvc1, rtVideo, xrtvc1, unknownFutureValue.
fields.name: VideoCodec

fields.description: True if the media stream bypassed the Mediation Server and went straight between client and PSTN Gateway/PBX, false otherwise.
fields.name: WasMediaBypassed
